        "cmip6.aerosol.key_properties.overview": {
            "values": [
                "MAM-3 has 3 modes of aerosols (Aitken, accumulation and coarse modes). Within a single mode, the mass mixing ratios of internally-mixed sulfate, ammonium, secondary organic aerosol (SOA), primary organic matter (POM) aged from the primary carbon mode, black carbon (BC) aged from the primary carbon mode, sea salt, and the number mixing ratio of accumulation mode particles are predicted. \n\nIn CMIP6 experiments, we used the identical aerosol model (MAM-3) in CAM5 and CESM1.2.\nHence, all contents are based on MAM-3 documents, \nespecially aerosol section in [Description of the NCAR Community Atmosphere Model (CAM 5.0)].\nThis dodument is available at [http://www.cesm.ucar.edu/models/cesm1.0/cam/docs/description/cam5_desc.pdf]."
            ]
        }, 
